The paper deals with the problem of binary classification of high dimensional data and introduces Bayesian models for the task. The methods are based on the graph formulation of semi-supervised learning, which is a common approach in machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses numerical methods for efficient sampling and estimation, which could fall under cs.SI (Systems and Control) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
